Consider the following code snippet from the text. Why is `this` required in the constructor?

```java
public SimpleTime(int hour, int minute, int second) {
    this.hour = hour;
    this.minute = minute;
    this.second = second;
}
```

Consider the following class snippet. If a client calls `new Time2()`, which constructor will be invoked?

```java
public class Time2 {
    public Time2() { this(0, 0, 0); }
    public Time2(int h, int m, int s) { /* initialization */ }
}
```
